@@TJvAppXMLStorageOptions.WhiteSpaceReplacement
Summary
  Indicates the string to use as a replacement for whitespaces in node names
Description
  The XML format does not allow whitespaces in node names. Should there be some in the names, then
  this value will be used to replace them. If it is empty, then an exception is triggered.

